-- Government Considering Additional $58 Billion Yen Stimulus, Nikkei Says
-- B y   C h r i s   C o o p e r
-- 2010-10-02T02:28:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-02/japan-considering-additional-58-billion-yen-stimulus-package-nikkei-says.html
Japan is considering an economic
stimulus package of about 4.8 trillion yen ($58 billion) as part
of an extra budget for this fiscal year, the Nikkei newspaper
said, without saying where it got the information. The
government will propose the package to opposition parties next
week, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
